    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-27T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.88/165a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-27T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>438. Please inform the Government to which you are accredited that Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RG2">George Rublee</persName> has been appointed by the United
                    States Government a co-member with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SRB1"
                        >Stevens</persName> on the Allied Maritime Transport Council. Repeat to
                    Paris as No. 5135 and Rome as No. 1591.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
